In this op-ed article, Vice President Mike Pence expresses his support for the people of Iran who are currently protesting for freedom and opportunity. He criticizes the previous Obama administration for not standing with the Iranian protesters during the Green Revolution in 2009, and he commends President Trump for swiftly offering support to the Iranian people. Pence mentions that the United States has already imposed sanctions on Iran's Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps and is considering additional actions to punish the regime. He calls on other freedom-loving nations to condemn Iran's dictators and defend the Iranian people's right to determine their own future. Pence concludes by stating that the United States stands with the people of Iran because it is right and because the regime threatens global peace and security.